text: Birdsview is an unincorporated community in Skagit County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Birdsview was established in 1881, and remained in operation until 1934. The community was named for Birdsey "Bird" Minkler, an early postmaster. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Skagit County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Birdsview, Washington
